    b"        Choose memory search hints for the selected task and current request.\x0d\x0a\x0d"
    b"\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a  "
    b"      Stop once the hints look good enough for the request without thinking abou"
    b"t it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. T"
    b"hey are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive te"
    b"xt fragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring against searchable"
    b" memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Each value is che"
    b"cked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a       "
    b" Optional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague r"
    b"emembered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Ru"
    b"les:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a       "
    b" - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0d\x0a     "
    b"     when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of"
    b" for positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibility"
    b" with older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclus"
    b"ions.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable words or phrases that should a"
    b"ppear\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.equals only fo"
    b"r exact text that should match a relevant\x0d\x0a          memory value as a whole.\x0d\x0a "
    b"       - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints over broad keyword stuffing.\x0d\x0a "
    b"       - Return empty arrays when no useful search hint is available.\x0d\x0a        -"
    b" Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        {{ _.role(\"user\") }}"
